{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: bundle-lab-report-eu_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates the top-level FSH Bundle instance for a complete HL7 Europe
    Laboratory Report (LAB) document. Unlike the EPS and HDR Bundle templates
    which drive dynamic entries from a `sections` dict, this template uses an
    explicit fixed structure with dedicated loops for specimens and observations,
    reflecting the fixed schema of a laboratory report.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: BundleLabReportEu
    Fixed elements:
      type = #document

  USAGE: #example — NOT #inline
    Same rationale as all Bundle templates. See bundle-eu-eps_fsh.twig.

  KEY DIFFERENCES FROM EPS AND HDR BUNDLES
    See the comparison table in bundle-eu-eps_fsh.twig. Specific to this template:

    1. ADDITIONAL FIXED ENTRIES: diagnosticReport AND serviceRequest
       The lab Bundle mandates two resources not present in EPS or HDR:
         entry[diagnosticReport] — the DiagnosticReport aggregating results
         entry[serviceRequest]   — the lab order that triggered the report
       Both use single named slices (no [+]/[=]) — exactly one per document.
       Note: slice names use camelCase capitalisation matching FHIR R4 resource
       type names: `diagnosticReport`, `serviceRequest`, `practitionerRole`.
       EPS and HDR use all-lowercase: `practitionerrole`, `organization`.

    2. NO SECTIONS DICT LOOP
       The EPS and HDR templates drive dynamic entries from the `sections`
       associative dict. The Lab Bundle has a fixed structure — no sections
       loop. Instead, dedicated loops handle the variable-length resource types:
         {% for s in specimenids %}  → entry[specimen][+]
         {% for r in results %}      → entry[observation][+]

    3. INSTANCE NAME ASSEMBLY BY TEMPLATE (not entry.instance)
       EPS and HDR rely on `entry.instance` (a pre-built FSH instance name
       provided by the caller) for `.resource` values in the sections loop.
       The Lab Bundle assembles all instance names directly in the template:
         Instance-Specimen-{{ s }}           (from specimenids UUID string)
         Instance-Observation-{{ r.instanceid }} (from results object)
       This means the naming convention is enforced by this template, not the
       caller — the caller must ensure upstream templates use matching names.

    4. REQUESTER VARIABLES — FLAT NAMING (not nested objects)
       EPS and HDR use nested object notation for provider resources:
         provider.instancerole, hospital.instancerole
       The Lab Bundle uses flat variable names for the requester:
         requesterrole  — UUID of the requester PractitionerRole
         requesterorg   — UUID of the requester Organisation
       These correspond to the `requester.*` variables in servicerequest- and
       provider-as-requester-eu-lab_fsh.twig but are passed as plain strings
       rather than nested object properties.

    5. FAKE ADD ONS ENTRIES — LABORATORY PROVIDER
       Two additional entries for the laboratory provider are marked as
       "FAKE ADD ONS" (mirroring the stub status of provider-as-laboratory_fsh.twig):
         entry[practitionerRole][+] — laboratory.instancerole
         entry[practitioner][+]     — laboratory.instancepractitioner
       These reference the placeholder resources from the laboratory provider
       template and should be replaced with real data when available.

  NAMED ENTRY SLICE CAPITALISATION
    The Lab Bundle profile uses camelCase slice names that match FHIR R4
    resource type names:
      diagnosticReport, serviceRequest, practitionerRole
    This differs from the EPS Bundle which uses lowercase:
      practitionerrole, organization
    The capitalisation must exactly match the profile's slice discriminator
    definitions — verify against the BundleLabReportEu StructureDefinition
    if SUSHI validation errors arise.

  SPECIMEN AND OBSERVATION LOOPS
    specimenids — array of UUID strings (same as in servicerequest and
                  diagnostic-report templates). Template builds the instance
                  name as `Instance-Specimen-{{ s }}`.
    results     — array of objects with `.instanceid`. Template builds the
                  instance name as `Instance-Observation-{{ r.instanceid }}`.
    Both loops produce named slices with [+]/[=] for the fullUrl/resource pair.

  PROVENANCE TAIL
    Identical to EPS and HDR: Device then Provenance as the final two
    unnamed [+]/[=] entries.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                             │ Type     │ Description                                  │
  ├──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ bundle.instanceid                    │ string   │ UUID for the Bundle resource.                │
  │ bundle.identifier                    │ string   │ Business identifier value.                   │
  │ composition.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Composition resource.            │
  │ composition.date                     │ string   │ FHIR dateTime string — no filter applied;    │
  │                                      │          │ must be pre-formatted by the caller.         │
  │ patient.instanceid                   │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                │
  │ patient.name                         │ string   │ Full display name (for patientdisplay only). │
  │ patient.age                          │ string   │ Pre-computed age string (for Description).   │
  │ diagnosticreport.instanceid          │ string   │ UUID of the DiagnosticReport resource.       │
  │ servicerequest.instanceid            │ string   │ UUID of the ServiceRequest resource.         │
  │ requesterrole                        │ string   │ UUID of the requester PractitionerRole.      │
  │                                      │          │ Flat variable — not nested as requester.*.   │
  │ requesterorg                         │ string   │ UUID of the requester Organisation.          │
  │                                      │          │ Flat variable — not nested as requester.*.   │
  │ specimenids                          │ string[] │ Array of Specimen resource UUIDs.            │
  │                                      │          │ Instance name assembled by template.         │
  │ results                              │ object[] │ Array of Observation result objects.         │
  │   [n].instanceid                     │ string   │   UUID; instance name assembled by template. │
  │ laboratory.instancerole              │ string   │ UUID of the laboratory PractitionerRole      │
  │                                      │          │ (FAKE ADD ONS — placeholder).               │
  │ laboratory.instancepractitioner      │ string   │ UUID of the laboratory Practitioner          │
  │                                      │          │ (FAKE ADD ONS — placeholder).               │
  │ provenance.deviceid                  │ string   │ UUID of the Device resource.                 │
  │ provenance.provenanceid              │ string   │ UUID of the Provenance resource.             │
  └──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the Bundle identifier system URI.

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-14
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Bundle-" ~ bundle.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: BundleLabReportEu
Title: "HL7 Europe Laboratory Report (LAB) Bundle"
{% set patientdisplay = patient.name ~ " (" ~ patient.age ~ " y/o) - synthetic data" %}
Description: "Complete HL7 Europe Laboratory Report (LAB) FHIR Bundle example for {{ patientdisplay }}"
Usage: #example

* id = "{{ bundle.instanceid }}"

* identifier.system = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier.value = "{{ bundle.identifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

* type = #document

{#
  Timestamp — NO date filter applied. Caller must supply a pre-formatted
  FHIR dateTime string. Differs from EPS/HDR which apply the datetime filter.
#}
* timestamp = "{{ composition.date|date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z')}}"

{#
  ── Fixed mandatory entries — single-slice ──────────────────────────────────
  Note: slice names use camelCase (diagnosticReport, serviceRequest,
  practitionerRole) matching FHIR R4 resource type names. EPS/HDR use
  lowercase (practitionerrole). Must match the profile's slice discriminators.
#}
* entry[composition].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ composition.instanceid }}"
* entry[composition].resource = Instance-Composition-{{ composition.instanceid }}

{# Lab-specific: aggregating DiagnosticReport (not present in EPS/HDR) #}
* entry[diagnosticReport].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ diagnosticreport.instanceid }}"
* entry[diagnosticReport].resource = Instance-DiagnosticReport-{{ diagnosticreport.instanceid }}

* entry[patient].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}"
* entry[patient].resource = Instance-Patient-{{ patient.instanceid }}

{# Lab-specific: the ServiceRequest (lab order) that triggered the report #}
* entry[serviceRequest].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ servicerequest.instanceid }}"
* entry[serviceRequest].resource = Instance-ServiceRequest-{{ servicerequest.instanceid }}

{#
  ── Requester entries — named multi-slices ───────────────────────────────────
  Note flat variable names: requesterrole and requesterorg (not nested objects).
  These correspond to requester.instancerole / requester.instanceorg in the
  upstream templates but are passed as plain strings to this Bundle template.
#}
* entry[practitionerRole][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ requesterrole }}"
* entry[practitionerRole][=].resource = Instance-PractitionerRole-{{ requesterrole }}

* entry[organization][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ requesterorg }}"
* entry[organization][=].resource = Instance-Organization-{{ requesterorg }}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  SPECIMEN ENTRIES — loop over plain UUID array
  specimenids is an array of UUID strings (not objects).
  Instance name assembled by template: Instance-Specimen-{{ s }}.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% for s in specimenids %}
* entry[specimen][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ s }}"
* entry[specimen][=].resource = Instance-Specimen-{{ s }}
{% endfor %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  OBSERVATION ENTRIES — loop over results object array
  results contains objects with .instanceid (same array as in the Composition
  and DiagnosticReport templates).
  Instance name assembled by template: Instance-Observation-{{ r.instanceid }}.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% for r in results %}
* entry[observation][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ r.instanceid }}"
* entry[observation][=].resource = Instance-Observation-{{ r.instanceid }}
{% endfor %}

{#
  ── Provenance tail — always last, unnamed slices (identical to EPS/HDR) ─────
#}
* entry[+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provenance.deviceid }}"
* entry[=].resource = Instance-Device-{{ provenance.deviceid }}
* entry[+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provenance.provenanceid }}"
* entry[=].resource = Instance-Provenance-{{ provenance.provenanceid }}

{#
  ── FAKE ADD ONS — laboratory provider entries ────────────────────────────────
  These placeholder entries reference the stub resources from
  provider-as-laboratory_fsh.twig. Marked FAKE ADD ONS in the original source.
  Replace with real laboratory provider data when available.
#}
{# FAKE ADD ONS - the laboratory organization and provider = legal attester #}
* entry[practitionerRole][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ laboratory.instancerole }}"
* entry[practitionerRole][=].resource = Instance-PractitionerRole-{{ laboratory.instancerole }}
* entry[practitioner][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ laboratory.instancepractitioner }}"
* entry[practitioner][=].resource = Instance-Practitioner-{{ laboratory.instancepractitioner }}
{# FAKE ADD ONS #}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
<!-- empty -->

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
